-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Our Guiding Philosophy</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>This is a problem worth solving.</em>  Too many valuable lives are being wasted. Homelessness caused by addiction is increasing in the LGBTQ community, a direct result of the use of drugs like crystal meth. They spend all their waking hours, every day trying to find a place to sleep. Combatting that homelessness by providing safe, stable transitional housing provides these members of the LGBTQ community the chance to start anew. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Our approach is built on personal experience. </em>You cannot craft a solution to a problem without truly understanding the issues at hand. We have that experience at <em>Restoring Pride</em>. Our co-founders have been homeless and suffered from addiction and from that experience have a deep understanding of the kind of approach that works.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>We are building an innovative solution that hasn’t been tried.</em> We are bringing everything together in one place: transitional housing and the ancillary services needed to start anew. We have seen too many lives wasted by the downward spiral of this epidemic. To stop the spiral, we must think differently, we must innovate and build a set of solutions that addresses who, what and how, and make those services easily accessible. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Our Core Values</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>People are fallible.&nbsp; We make mistakes. We believe every person has the right to be truly happy, no matter what happiness looks like to them, and to start their lives anew.</li><li>We believe that homelessness among members of the LGBTQ community suffering from addiction is the worst epidemic to strike the community since the AIDS crisis of the 1980s.</li><li>We believe that the LGBTQ community must take responsibility for epidemic and not continue to marginalize and ignore this segment of our community.</li><li>We believe that every person who identifies as LGBTQ and is suffering from addiction and is homeless, deserves a second chance, with no questions asked.</li><li>We believe that the first step to beginning anew is the acquisition of safe, stable housing and each resident has the same rights and responsibilities as any person in this country.</li><li>We believe that drug rehabilitation is critical but only when the individual is ready and that sobriety should not be a barrier to acquiring safe, stable housing.&nbsp;</li><li>We believe it must be the goal of each resident, following completion of this program, to successfully transition themselves back into the community and begin anew.</li><li>We believe every resident has a right to refuse medical care and/or treatment if they choose to and are physically capable of making that choice.</li><li>We are committed to offering a foundation of mental health and other social services to each resident.</li><li>We believe it is the responsibility of each resident to determine and seek out any and all additional needs or specific problem areas that builds on their individual treatment plans.&nbsp;</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->','What We Do','','inherit','closed','closed','','7-revision-v1','','','2019-08-10 10:34:58','2019-08-10 09:34:58','',7,'https://restoringpride:8890/7-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(106,1,'2019-08-10 10:36:07','2019-08-10 09:36:07','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Restoring Pride, Inc.</em> is a non-profit organization providing safe, stable transitional housing for members of the LGBTQ community dealing with homelessness brought on by addiction. We will establish self-sustaining villages that offer accommodations for up to a year to members of the LGBTQ community who have found themselves homeless due to addiction. These villages offer counseling and other remediation services, minor medica