ion is critical but only when the individual is ready and that sobriety should not be a barrier to acquiring safe, stable housing. </li><li>We believe it must be the goal of each resident, following completion of this program, to successfully transition themselves back into the community and begin anew.</li><li>We believe every resident has a right to refuse medical care and/or treatment if they choose to and are physically capable of making that choice.</li><li>We are committed to offering a foundation of mental health and other social services to each resident.</li><li>We believe it is the responsibility of each resident to determine and seek out any and all additional needs or specific problem areas that builds on their individual treatment plans. </li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->','What We Do','','inherit','closed','closed','','7-revision-v1','','','2019-08-10 11:11:38','2019-08-10 10:11:38','',7,'https://restoringpride:8890/7-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(131,1,'2019-08-13 19:52:16','2019-08-13 18:52:16','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We take web accessibility seriously. We believe that the web should be open, free and accessible to all, regardless of ability or impairment. We follow the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG/\">Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.0</a>&nbsp;guidelines and work hard to achieve AA conformance.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Adherence to guidelines</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We go the extra mile to make our web pages accessible. Here are a few ways in which we do this:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>We avoid using text in images where possible, and always try to include text to describe image content</li><li>Content is separated by appropriate headings for ease of reading by humans and screen reading software</li><li>Web pages may be navigated by keyboard, and links are appropriately highlighted on focus</li><li>Hyperlinks are as descriptive a