wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Founded in 2019, <em>Restoring Pride</em> will provide housing for up to 100 people for a period of one year, as well as unrestricted access to the medical/social services that they may require.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->','About Us','','inherit','closed','closed','','9-revision-v1','','','2019-09-30 21:45:51','2019-09-30 20:45:51','',9,'https://restoringpride.org/9-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(262,2,'2019-09-30 21:56:02','2019-09-30 20:56:02','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Lynn Reyes is an organizational change maker for public sector and private sector organizations, aligning strategy at the intersection where people, business, information, and technology meet. She is a tireless advocate for inclusion, equal rights, civil rights, and the less fortunate of the world who have been left behind. Lynn began her career at The World Bank as an analyst for the Asia Region. She has spent the last 18 years at IBM, first as a consultant and a managing consultant on innovation, strategy and business transformation for IBM Global Services and next joined the IBM Institute of Business Value as the Public Sector Director. She recently finished a four year stint in Dubai with IBM Middle East and Africa. She is currently a Global Eminence Program Leader at the IBM IBV. She has an MBA from the University of Maryland Robert H. Smith School of Business. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Lynn Reyes','','inherit','closed','closed','','254-revision-v1','','','2019-09-30 21:56:02','2019-09-30 20:56:02','',254,'https://restoringpride.org/254-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(264,2,'2019-09-30 22:18:30','2019-09-30 21:18:30','<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Our vision...</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:columns -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns has-2-columns\"><!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To see an end to chronic homeless once and for all.  Where all members of the LGBTQ community have unrestricted access to stable housing as well as the services needed to become self-sufficient once again.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Founded in 2019, Restoring Pride stands out among the services available today.  Clients are back in control during their recovery.  We cannot force recovery on someone and expect it work in the long term.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->','About Us','','inherit','closed','closed','','9-revision-v1','','','2019-09-30 22:18:30','2019-09-30 21:18:30','',9,'https://restoringpride.org/9-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(265,2,'2019-09-30 22:19:11','2019-09-30 21:19:11','<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Our vision...</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:columns -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns has-2-columns\"><!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To see an end to chronic homeless once and for all.&nbsp; Where all members of the LGBTQ community have unrestricted access to stable housing as well as the services needed to become self-sufficient once again.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Founded in 2019, Restoring Pride stands out among the services available today. &nbsp;Clients are back in control during their recovery.&nbsp; We cannot force recovery on someone and expect it work in the long term.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->','About Us','','inherit','closed','closed','','9-revision-v1','','','2019-09-30 22:19:11','2019-09-30 21:19:11','',9,'https://restoringpride.org/9-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(266,2,'2019-09-30 22:30:20','2019-09-30 21:30:20','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Restoring Pride, Inc. is a non-profit organization providing safe, stable transitional housing for members of the LGBTQ community dealing with homelessness brought on by addiction. </h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We will establish self-sustaining villages that offer accommodations for up to a year to members of the LGBTQ community who have found themselves homeless due to addiction. These villages offer counseling and other remediation services, minor medical services and a host of other solutions, co-located within the facility.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:columns {\"className\":\"no-margin-xs\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns has-2-columns no-margin-xs\"><!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Case Management</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Personal Action Plan</li><li>Crisis navigation</li><li>Job placement assistance</li><li>Community referrals</li><li>Health and wellness support</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Supportive Services</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Medical Care</li><li>Mental Health Services</li><li>Legal support</li><li>HIV/STI testing</li><li>Substance abuse treatment</li><li>Personal hygiene and self-care</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->\n\n<!-- wp:columns -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns has-2-columns\"><!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Skills Development</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Education (GED, High School, College or Job Training)</li><li>Life skills</li><li>Budgeting and financial literacy</li><li>Meal preparation classes</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Social Support</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Program specific support groups</li><li>Peer-led support network</li><li>Access to LGBTQ programming</li><li>Community outings and engagement</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Our Guiding Philosophy</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>This is a problem worth solving.</em> &nbsp;Too many valuable lives are being wasted. Homelessness caused by addiction is increasing in the LGBTQ community, a direct result of the use of drugs like crystal meth. They spend all their waking hours, every day trying to find a place to sleep. Combatting that homelessness by providing safe, stable transitional housing provides these members of the LGBTQ community the chance to start anew.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":18,\"align\":\"right\",\"width\":300,\"height\":171} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"alignright is-resized\"><img src=\"https://restoringpride.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/jonathan-rados-Sbxt82CsMxA-unsplash-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"Bearded homeless man holding his head\" class=\"wp-image-18\" width=\"300\" height=\"171\"/><figcaption>Homelessness caused by addiction is increasing in the LGBTQ community</figcaption></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Our approach is built on personal experience. </strong>You cannot craft a solution to a problem without truly understanding the issues at hand. We have that experience at <em>Restoring Pride</em>. Our co-founders have been homeless and suffered from addiction and from that experience have a deep understanding of the kind of approach that works.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>We are building an innovative solution that hasn’t been tried.</strong> We are bringing everything together in one place: transitional housing and the ancillary services needed to start anew. We have seen too many lives wasted by the downward spiral of this epidemic. To stop the spiral, we must think differently, we must innovate and build a set of solutions that addresses who, what and how, and make those services easily accessible.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Our Core Values</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>People are fallible. We believe that every person has the right to be truly happy, no matter what happiness looks like to them.  Stability is the cornerstone to being happy in life.</li><li>We believe that homelessness among members of the LGBTQ community caused by crystal meth addiction is the worst epidemic to strike the community since the AIDS crisis of the 1980s.</li><li>The LGBTQ community must take responsibility for this epidemic and discontinue ignoring the problem and marginalizing this segment of the community.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>We believe every person has the right to be truly happy, no matter what happiness looks like to them, and to start their lives anew.</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>We believe that every person who identifies as LGBTQ and is suffering from addiction and is homeless, deserves a second chance, with no questions asked.</li><li>We believe that the first step to beginning anew is the acquisition of safe, stable housing and each resident has the same rights and responsibilities as any person in this country.</li><li>We believe that drug rehabilitation is critical but only when the individual is ready and that sobriety should not be a barrier to acquiring safe, stable housing.&nbsp;</li><li>We believe it must be the goal of each resident, following completion of this program, to successfully transition themselves back into the community and begin anew.</li><li>We believe every resident has a right to refuse medical care and/or treatment if they choose to and are physically capable of making that choice.</li><li>We are committed to offering a foundation of mental health and other social services to each resident.</li><li>We believe it is the responsibility of each resident to determine and seek out any and all additional needs or specific problem areas that builds on their individual treatment plans.&nbsp;</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->','What We Do','','inherit','closed','closed','','7-revision-v1','','','2019-09-30 22:30:20','2019-09-30 21:30:20','',7,'https://restoringpride.org/7-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(267,2,'2019-09-30 22:31:59','2019-09-30 21:31:59','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Restoring Pride, Inc. is a non-profit organization providing safe, stable transitional housing for members of the LGBTQ community dealing with homelessness brought on by addiction. </h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We will establish self-sustaining villages that offer accommodations for up to a year to members of the LGBTQ community who have found themselves homeless or without stable housing. These villages offer counseling and other remediation services, minor medical services and a host of other solutions, co-located within the facility.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:columns {\"className\":\"no-margin-xs\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns has-2-columns no-margin-xs\"><!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Case Management</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Personal Action Plan</li><li>Crisis navigation</li><li>Job placement assistance</li><li>Community referrals</li><li>Health and wellness support</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Supportive Services</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:lis